# Github Resources

1. [Install Github bash on Windows](https://r-bio.github.io/git-installation/)
1. [Creating an ssh key](https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/generating-a-new-ssh-key-and-adding-it-to-the-ssh-agent). 
1. [Registering your ssh key with Github](https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh/adding-a-new-ssh-key-to-your-github-account).
1. [Creating a Github Personal Authentication Token (PAT)](https://usethis.r-lib.org/articles/git-credentials.html)
1. CI/CD testing and coverage.
    - `use_github_action_check_standard()`
    - `use_github_actions_badge()`
    - `use_coverage()`
    - `use_readme_rmd()`
1. Setting up miniconda
    - install `reticulate`
    - installing a python environment


